did.abstract: Research materials and sound recordings pertaining to Cole Porter

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: The William McBrien Papers were established in the Music Library of Yale University by William McBrien in 2003.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The collection is open to researchers by appointment. There are no restricted materials in the collection. Please contact the Special Collections staff to schedule an appointment.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: The William McBrien Papers are the physical property of the Irving S. Gilmore Music Library of Yale University. Copyrights belong to the composers and authors, or their legal heirs and assigns.

relatedmaterial.head: Associated Materials
relatedmaterial.p: Researchers interested in Cole Porter may wish to consult MSS 82, the Cole Porter Collection at Yale, and also the Cole Porter Collection in the Music Division of the Library of Congress.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: MSS 131, The William McBrien Papers in the Irving S. Gilmore Music Library of Yale University.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: William McBrien (1930-2009) was a professor of English at Hofstra University. He wrote biographies of Cole Porter and Stevie Smith.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: William McBrien's papers pertain chiefly to Cole Porter, and arise mainly from the research for his book Cole Porter: A Biography (New York: Knopf, 1998). They include research materials, sound recordings, and other items. McBrien's original arrangement has largely been preserved, so some topics are covered in more than one series. A few items have been re-labeled or re-filed for the sake of clarity.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The collection is organized into five series, as follows: I. Notecards. II. Glossary of Names. III. Porter Chronology. IV. Research Topics. V. Sound Recordings.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series consists of McBrien's notecards from his research on Cole Porter. Sub-series I.A is arranged alphabetically by name, and Sub-series I.B is arranged alphabetically by topic.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains background information on numerous people associated with Porter, arranged alphabetically.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains information about Porter's life, arranged chronologically. It was originally kept in two binders. Each binder also included additional materials with no clear relationship to the chronology; these have been placed in two folders marked Miscellaneous.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains materials on various topics relating to Porter. It covers much of the same ground as Series I, II, and III, but Series IV has more extensive information on each topic. It appears to be McBrien's raw material, while the other Series seem to reflect his efforts to transform it into a book.

scopecontent.p: Sound recordings have been transferred to the Historical Sound Recordings Collection in the Music Library. For further information, please contact the Curator of Historical Sound Recordings.
